# Fishhawk local-dev environment variables.
#
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in the values you need:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The Makefile auto-includes .env if present, so `make dev-backend`
# picks these up without `set -a; source .env; set +a` plumbing.
#
# `fishhawkd` ignores any variable that isn't set, but it logs a
# warning on startup for each missing piece (OAuth, webhooks, etc.).
# See docs/github-app/README.md for the local-dev modes that
# determine which of these you need.

# --- core (required) ---

# Postgres connection string. Matches docker-compose.yml.
FISHHAWKD_DATABASE_URL=postgres://fishhawk:fishhawk@localhost:5432/fishhawk?sslmode=disable

# Listen address. Defaults to :8080 if unset; uncomment to override.
# FISHHAWKD_ADDR=:8080

# --- acceptance preview least-privilege role (E31.19 / #1577) ---
# `scripts/dev preview` runs the UNTRUSTED merge-candidate binary against a
# throwaway <dbname>_preview database using a dedicated non-superuser role —
# NOT the operator credential above — that owns only that database and is denied
# CONNECT to the dev database. Defaults below; override only if the default
# role name/password collides on a shared Postgres. An overridden password MUST
# be URL-safe (it is spliced into the preview DATABASE_URL).
# FISHHAWK_PREVIEW_DB_ROLE=fishhawk_preview
# FISHHAWK_PREVIEW_DB_PASSWORD=fishhawk_preview

# --- background workers ---
# Off by default so dev runs aren't racing the timer/watchdog.

# FISHHAWKD_ENABLE_SLA_TIMER=true
# FISHHAWKD_ENABLE_DISPATCH_WATCHDOG=true

# --- GitHub App (Mode B / C in docs/github-app/README.md) ---
# Without these, /webhooks/github responds 503 and dispatch is disabled.

# FISHHAWKD_GITHUB_APP_ID=123456
# FISHHAWKD_GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY_FILE=/path/to/private-key.pem
# FISHHAWKD_GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=...

# --- OAuth sign-in (Mode B / C) ---
# All three must be set together; mismatch fails fast.
# Without these, /v0/auth/github/* responds 503.

# FISHHAWKD_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=Iv1.xxxx
# FISHHAWKD_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# FISHHAWKD_OAUTH_CALLBACK_URL=http://localhost:8080/v0/auth/github/callback
# FISHHAWKD_OAUTH_REDIRECT_AFTER_LOGIN=http://localhost:5173/

# --- SPA root for back-links (#231) ---
# Used as `details_url` on the published `fishhawk_audit_complete`
# GitHub Check Run so a reviewer who clicks the check on github.com
# lands on the run page in Fishhawk. Vite serves the SPA on :5173 in
# local dev. Empty disables the publish-to-GitHub path cleanly; the
# in-Fishhawk gate enforcement still works.

# FISHHAWKD_EXTERNAL_URL=http://localhost:5173

# --- runner OIDC (only when iterating on the signing-key endpoint) ---
# Off by default — endpoint accepts any caller (v0 self-execution
# posture). Set to a non-empty audience to enforce verification.

# FISHHAWKD_OIDC_AUDIENCE=fishhawkd-local
# FISHHAWKD_OIDC_JWKS_URL=https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com/.well-known/jwks

# --- trace storage (S3 / MinIO) ---
# Without FISHHAWKD_S3_BUCKET, /v0/runs/{id}/trace responds 503.
# docker-compose.yml ships a MinIO instance on :9000; run
# `make minio-init` to create the bucket, then uncomment the four
# lines below to wire it in.

# FISHHAWKD_S3_BUCKET=fishhawk-traces
# FISHHAWKD_S3_REGION=us-east-1
# FISHHAWKD_S3_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:9000
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=fishhawk
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=fishhawk-dev-secret

# --- OTel trace export (opt-in, #649/#679) ---
# The runner emits a per-run GenAI trace (a `stage <name>` span with a
# `chat <model>` child carrying gen_ai.* + fishhawk.* cost/repro attrs)
# ONLY when OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT is set; unset is a clean no-op,
# so the default loop is unaffected (runner gates emission on this var,
# runner/internal/otelemit/otelemit.go).
#
# http://localhost:4318 points at the compose `otel`-profile Jaeger
# (`docker compose --profile otel up -d`); view traces at
# http://localhost:16686.
#
# CAVEAT: the endpoint must be reachable from wherever the runner
# ACTUALLY executes. The standard dogfood loop dispatches the runner to
# a GitHub-hosted CI runner, where `localhost:4318` is the CI host's
# loopback — NOT this machine. End-to-end local viewing therefore
# requires the runner to run on a host that can reach this collector
# (invoke fishhawk-runner locally). See docs/ARCHITECTURE.md §10
# (local OTLP collector row) for the verification path.

# OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:4318

# --- plan review (ADR-027) ---
# Per-invocation timeout for plan/implement review agent calls. The code
# default is 300s (#606) — sized to cover review of large standard_v1 plans.
# Leave this commented to inherit that default. Setting a value BELOW 300s
# risks timing out large plans (the reviewer is killed mid-review and the
# stage records a *_review_failed audit entry); fishhawkd logs a startup WARN
# if the effective value is under the 300s floor.
# FISHHAWKD_PLAN_REVIEW_TIMEOUT=300s
